<s> The first paragraph of the Introduction in RFC2368 not withstanding, I think both documents identify an action ("send mail this way", or "send an sms this way") instead of actual mailboxes or end points.  </s>
<s> I would prefer documents to be precise about what they actually identify but as long as they do so and people use the identifier in a way consistent with that statement then I think its ok....  </s>
<s> In other words, the SMS document has it right: the URI here identifies and "SMS message" not the end point for an SMS message.  </s>
<s> An end point is needed as part of an "SMS message" in order to be meaninful but it isn't the end point that's being identified.  </s>
<s> In many cases people have been using mailto:foo@bar.com  </s>
<s> to identify the human user who currently 'uses' that mailbox and IMHO, that's also a serious semantic mistake... -MM  </s>
